2. Fetch Types: Lazy vs Eager

LAZY (default for collections): Data is loaded only when you access it.
EAGER (default for @OneToOne, @ManyToOne): Data is loaded immediately with the parent entity.

Example:

@OneToMany(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)
private List<Post> posts;

@ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.EAGER)
private User user;
Best Practice:
Use LAZY for collections to avoid unnecessary data loading and performance issues.

3. Configuring @JoinTable and @JoinColumn

@JoinColumn:
Used for single-column foreign keys (e.g., @ManyToOne, @OneToOne).
@JoinTable:
Used for join tables in @ManyToMany relationships.

Example:

// In Many-to-Many
@ManyToMany
@JoinTable(
    name = "student_course",
    joinColumns = @JoinColumn(name = "student_id"),
    inverseJoinColumns = @JoinColumn(name = "course_id")
)
private Set<Course> courses;

